  "prompt": "A large gym brand have allowed me to sell their service and I would like to market it . Should I seek their permission?",
  "response": "Yes, you should definitely seek their explicit permission and clarification before marketing their service. Here's why and what you should do:\n\n1. Verify Marketing Rights\n- Confirm the specific terms of your agreement\n- Request clear guidelines on how you can promote their service\n- Ask about approved marketing materials and messaging\n\n2. Get Written Authorization\n- Request written permission for marketing activities\n- Clarify what marketing channels you can use\n- Understand any restrictions or compliance requirements\n\n3. Check Brand Guidelines\n- Ask for their official brand marketing guidelines\n- Ensure you're using logos, colors, and messaging correctly\n- Understand their standards for representing their brand\n\n4. Potential Marketing Approvals\n- Some brands require pre-approval of marketing content\n- They might want to review your advertising materials\n- Ensure you follow their specific protocols\n\n5. Legal Considerations\n- Verify you have the right to sell and market their service\n- Understand any contractual obligations\n- Confirm commission structures and marketing permissions\n\n6. Best Practices\n- Be transparent about your relationship with the gym brand\n- Use accurate and honest marketing language\n- Represent their service professionally\n\nSeeking explicit permission protects both you and the gym brand, and ensures you're marketing their service appropriately.",
